[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man charged with murder bid in Gilmerton pub

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has been charged with attempted murder after a man was seriously injured in an Edinburgh pub.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
A 28-year-old man was attacked in the Mechanic Arms in Drum Street at about 14:40 on Sunday.
A 60-year-old was arrested in Essex on Wednesday in connection with the incident and is due to appear at Edinburgh Sheriff Court on Friday.
Officers said the 28-year-old man's injuries were not life-threatening. Police are appealing for witnesses.
